            <fr:title text="Closure">Closure</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Munkres <fr:link href="/munkres-2000-topology/" title="Topology" uri="http://localhost:8000/munkres-2000-topology/" display-uri="munkres-2000-topology" type="local">Topology</fr:link> Section 17</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X,\mathcal {T})]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gt-0002/" title="Topological space" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-0002/" display-uri="gt-0002" type="local">Topological space</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E\subseteq  X]]></fr:tex>. We define the <html:dfn>Closure</html:dfn> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> to be the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\overline {E}]]></fr:tex> equal to the intersection of all closed sets containing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>,
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\overline {E}:=\bigcap \{F\mid  F\hbox { is closed}, E\subseteq  F\}.]]></fr:tex></html:p>
            <html:p>Note that other possible notations for the closure of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> includes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {Cl}}(E)]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
