            <fr:title text="Continuous Function">Continuous Function</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Munkres <fr:link href="/munkres-2000-topology/" title="Topology" uri="http://localhost:8000/munkres-2000-topology/" display-uri="munkres-2000-topology" type="local">Topology</fr:link> Section 18</fr:meta>
            <fr:meta name="source">MML <fr:link href="https://mizar.uwb.edu.pl/version/current/html/tops_2.html#T43" type="external">tops_2:43</fr:link></fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X,\mathcal {T_{1}})]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(Y,\mathcal {T}_{2})]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="/gt-0002/" title="Topological space" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-0002/" display-uri="gt-0002" type="local">Topological space</fr:link>s. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to  Y]]></fr:tex> be a function, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex>. We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <html:dfn>Continuous at a point</html:dfn> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> if for any <fr:link href="/gt-0003/" title="Neighborhood" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-0003/" display-uri="gt-0003" type="local">Neighborhood</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex>, there is a <fr:link href="/gt-0003/" title="Neighborhood" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-0003/" display-uri="gt-0003" type="local">Neighborhood</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(U)\subseteq  V]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <html:dfn>Continuous</html:dfn> if it is continuous at each point of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
