            <fr:title text="Hausdorff space">Hausdorff space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Munkres <fr:link href="/munkres-2000-topology/" title="Topology" uri="http://localhost:8000/munkres-2000-topology/" display-uri="munkres-2000-topology" type="local">Topology</fr:link> Section 17</fr:meta>
            <fr:meta name="source">MML <fr:link href="https://mizar.uwb.edu.pl/version/current/html/pre_topsc.html#V8" type="external">pre_topsc:def 10</fr:link></fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X,\mathcal {T})]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gt-0002/" title="Topological space" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-0002/" display-uri="gt-0002" type="local">Topological space</fr:link>. We say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <html:dfn>Hausdorff</html:dfn> if for any two distinct points <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in  X]]></fr:tex>, there are disjoint open sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U,V\subseteq  X]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  U]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  V]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>12</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>remark</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>The literature also calls this the <html:dfn><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[T_{2}]]></fr:tex> Property</html:dfn>.</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
