            <fr:title text="Properties of closed subsets">Properties of closed subsets</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">Munkres <fr:link href="/munkres-2000-topology/" title="Topology" uri="http://localhost:8000/munkres-2000-topology/" display-uri="munkres-2000-topology" type="local">Topology</fr:link> Theorem 17.1</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X,\mathcal {T})]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gt-0002/" title="Topological space" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-0002/" display-uri="gt-0002" type="local">Topological space</fr:link>. If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex> is the collection of closed subsets of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, then the following all hold:</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X\in \mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\emptyset \in \mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li>Intersection of arbitrary family of closed sets is closed: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigcap \{F_{\alpha }\in \mathcal {F}\mid \alpha \in  I\}\in \mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li>Union of finitely-many closed sets is closed: If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F_{1},…,F_{n}\in \mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F_{1}\cup …\cup  F_{n}\in \mathcal {F}]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
